(c)
Fig. 33. Application entry screens. (a) Splash screen displaying application branding during initialization; (b) Home screen with primary navigation options for prediction and history access; (c) Optional onboarding guide introducing the staged input workflow with option to skip on future launches.
First-time users were presented with an optional onboarding guide (Fig. 33c) that introduced the staged input workflow, addressing the digital literacy constraints where 100% of interviewed farmers reported no prior agricultural application usage (Table 6, Theme I12). The onboarding screen implemented in PredictPalayActivity included a "Don't show again" checkbox stored via SharedPreferences that allowed experienced users to bypass the introduction on subsequent launches, balancing accessibility for novices with efficiency for repeat users.
The prediction workflow began with pre-planting data entry (Fig. 34a), implemented through PrePlantingActivity, which collected fundamental farm characteristics: land area in hectares, rice variety selection via dropdown, seed amount in
 
 
